mdElement.text: Q: Do the hardware POST results persist so that they are available to the FS1553 asset should it re-enter the Initialize state through one of the other states? If not then an attempt to reinitialize will result in the BITFailed state.
NOTE: Behavior is identical to US1553 asset.
FC-7753 which is an internal activity is not modeled
Not modeled - an internal transition to Lock out all commands other than Rotation of S&A Devices (Req FC-7752)
I am not entirely confident that this is the right sub-state machine. The requirements are ambiguous as to the internal states. Revisit this when the new requirements are distributed.

Not sure whether this transition should originate from substate Initialization/Idle or from the Initialization superstate. Bc autocoder may not handle group transitions, attached this to a specific sub-state.

Upon TST_GbE_BIT_Completes event, two things are supposed to happen, one is a function and the other is a state transition. I wasn't sure how to model this. Opted for having two internal transitions that fire on the same event. One calls the function, the other generates an event that causes a transition from the current state back to Initialization/Idle.

There is a Power_Up state on the state transition document however it had no transition label - further evidence that Power_Up shouldn't be a state. It is not included here, for this reason, and because the autocoder has a rule that all transitions must have labels.
There is no requirements section for this state. Requirements for entry actions for this state appear in the Failed mode section. Perhaps this state should be folded into the Failed state?
